CREATE procedure [dbo].[testing_status] @t_testing_id uniqueidentifier
as declare @t_workstation_id uniqueidentifier
declare @status varchar(10) declare @step int declare @test_num int declare @t_test_id uniqueidentifier declare @current_step_id uniqueidentifier declare @last_step_id uniqueidentifier declare @lang_num int declare @lang_short_code varchar(3) declare @firstname nvarchar(100) declare @secondname nvarchar(100) declare @perscode char(12) declare @test_name nvarchar(100) declare @step_num nvarchar(100) declare @step_count int
declare @back_btn_mark char(1) declare @question_btn_mark char(1) declare @CURRENT_STOP_TIME datetime declare @stop_time_sec int declare @stop_times int declare @count_stop_times int declare @time_limit_min int declare @seconds_remain int declare @show_question_mark char(1) declare @jsfile varchar(50)
set @back_btn_mark ='n'
select @t_workstation_id=t.t_workstation_id, @status=ts.obj_name from t_testing t inner join t_testing_status ts on t.t_testing_status_id = ts.t_testing_status_id where t_testing_id=@t_testing_id
end else begin select @status=obj_name from t_testing_status ts inner join t_testing t on ts.t_testing_status_id = t.t_testing_status_id where t.t_testing_id = @t_testing_id

end
select @lang_num= tl.lang_num, @lang_short_code= tl.lang_short_code from t_testing t inner join t_testing_language tl on t.t_testing_language_id = tl.t_testing_language_id where t.t_testing_id=@t_testing_id

begin
select @t_test_id= current_test_id from t_testing where t_testing_id = @t_testing_id
select @current_step_id=current_step_id from t_testing_test where t_testing_id = @t_testing_id and t_test_id = @t_test_id

select @step_num=ts.step_num,@step=ts.step_order, @jsfile=isnull(js.file_name,'') from t_test_step ts left outer join t_test_step_js_file js on ts.t_test_step_js_file_id=js.t_test_step_js_file_id where ts.t_test_step_id=@current_step_id

begin
--set @seconds_remain=200
select @start_time=min(isnull(ts.view_date,getdate())) --ts.view_date, ,@STOP_TIME_SEC=min(isnull(tt.STOP_TIME_SEC,0)) from t_testing_step ts inner join t_test_step s on ts.t_test_step_id=s.t_test_step_id inner join t_testing_test tt on s.t_test_id=tt.t_test_id where s.t_test_id=@t_test_id and ts.t_testing_id=@t_testing_id and tt.t_testing_id=@t_testing_id
